{"_id":"post-b83c65b8-f61b-4ed5-9ab4-b3b7fcdcb1c7","_type":"post","title":"Terminal Links","slug":{"_type":"slug","current":"terminal-links"},"body":[{"_key":"538ea5c20da1","children":[{"_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"Terminals make it hard to copy things: Selecting text works differently to what people are used to, and ","_key":"538ea5c20da10"},{"_type":"span","marks":["code"],"text":"^C","_key":"538ea5c20da11"},{"_type":"span","marks":[],"text":" aborts the current program. Links are hard to use.","_key":"538ea5c20da12"}],"markDefs":[],"_type":"block","style":"normal"},{"_key":"6db52b1decc9","children":[{"_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"Now you can click on links in the repl.it terminal.","_key":"6db52b1decc90"}],"markDefs":[],"_type":"block","style":"normal"},{"_key":"24788c1788f2","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"24788c1788f20","text":"","marks":[]}],"markDefs":[],"_type":"block","style":"normal"},{"_key":"b587f49f5277","children":[{"_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"It's as simple as starting a repl and printing a URL to the terminal.","_key":"b587f49f52770"}],"markDefs":[],"_type":"block","style":"normal"},{"_key":"5fea83c7a233","children":[{"_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"This is super helpful with languages like Rust, which often print URLs in error messages to help you debug and learn.","_key":"5fea83c7a2330"}],"markDefs":[],"_type":"block","style":"normal"},{"_key":"f211f1d3ac91","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"f211f1d3ac910","text":"","marks":[]}],"markDefs":[],"_type":"block","style":"normal"},{"_key":"8fbd814eb51e","children":[{"_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"This also works on repl.run, where you can ","_key":"8fbd814eb51e0"},{"_type":"span","marks":["7615657fd1e1"],"text":"publish terminal apps as websites","_key":"8fbd814eb51e1"},{"_type":"span","marks":[],"text":". As an example, here's the repl.it blog available on repl.run ","_key":"8fbd814eb51e2"},{"_type":"span","marks":["ac0e69e64cf8"],"text":"as a terminal website","_key":"8fbd814